OL,3,CDisabled to get 'right to try' work
OL,4,Cwithout risk of losing benefits
OL,6,FDisabled people will have the right to
OL,7,Ftry employment without the risk of
OL,8,Flosing their benefits under plans set
OL,9,Fto be announced as part of the
OL,10,FGovernment's welfare reforms.
OL,12,FWork and Pensions Secretary Liz
OL,13,FKendall is expected to announce
OL,14,Flegislation to introduce a "right to
OL,15,Ftry guarantee" that will prevent
OL,16,Fpeople receiving health-related
OL,17,Fbenefits from having their
OL,18,Fentitlements automatically re-assessed
OL,19,Fif they enter employment.
