OL,3,CDisabled to get 'right to try' work
OL,4,Cwithout risk of losing benefits
OL,6,FThe move is said to be in response to
OL,7,Fsurveys suggesting disabled people and
OL,8,Fthose with long-term health conditions
OL,9,Ffear they will not get their benefits
OL,10,Fback if they try employment, but it
OL,11,Fdoes not work out.
OL,13,FA recent Department for Work and
OL,14,FPensions (DWP) survey found 200,000
OL,15,Fpeople receiving health-related or
OL,16,Fdisability benefits were ready to work
OL,17,Fif the right job or support was
OL,18,Favailable.
