OL,6,FDowning Street has warned that without
OL,7,Faction, benefits will "swallow more
OL,8,Ftaxpayers' money and leave more people
OL,9,Ftrapped in a life of unemployment and
OL,10,Finactivity".
OL,12,FChancellor Rachel Reeves has
OL,13,Fpreviously said the Government must
OL,14,F"get a grip" on benefits, but
OL,15,Funcertainty about Labour's plans have
OL,16,Fled to some of the party's
OL,17,Fbackbenchers to express concern about
OL,18,Fthe potential impact on disabled
OL,19,Fpeople.
